item.description:
@Im_Key wrote:

The second problem is somewhat incredibly easy as you’re only changing a number, but you must find it first…

AGS spec problem is slightly harder, chances are if you have a recent/updated client that it already has the GFX model in there somewhere, because most clients these days have everything. You just have to change the GFX id in your source.

item.description:
@Im_Key wrote:

Well the AGS spec is client sided, adding the model gfx and then applying it to your source.

The teleport GFX is server sided, just a matter of changing 369 to whatever the teleport GFX is.
